{"name": "halohome", "metadata": {"name": "halohome", "version": "0.6.0", "classifiers": ["Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://github.com/nayaverdier/halohome", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["aiohttp", "bleak", "csrmesh"], "summary": "A python library to control Eaton HALO Home Smart Lights", "upload_time": 1732325119}, "documentation": ["# halohome\n\nA python library to control Eaton HALO Home Smart Lights\n\n\n# Changelog\n\n## 0.6.0 2024-11-22\n\nCourtesy of @oyvindkinsey:\n\n- Update the use of Avi-on's API to the current v3\n- Fix incorrect use of avid (this now also supports groups etc)\n- Add new function for constructing packets that work for both devices and groups\n- Remove use of deprecated BLEDevices.rssi\n- Replaced product_ids filtering with a type filter\n\n## 0.5.0 2022-01-25\n\n- Sort devices by RSSI before connecting to avoid unnecessary delay\n\n## 0.4.0 2021-11-08\n\n(BREAKING)\n\n- Remove support for `user_id` (username/email is sufficient)\n- Support offline loading of devices (e.g. in case of internet outage)\n\n## 0.3.0 2021-10-25\n\n- Read `user_id` to provide a permanent ID for the HALO Home account\n\n## 0.2.1 2021-10-23\n\n- Raise HaloHomeError when credentials are not valid\n\n## 0.2.0 2021-10-21\n\n- Support mesh communication (only need to connect to a single device\n  to control all of them)\n- Make network and bluetooth connections async\n\n## 0.1.0 2021-10-17\n\n- Initial release\n"], "modules": [{"name": "halohome", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "halohome._format_mac_address", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "mac_address", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "halohome._make_request", "asynchronous": true